p.span: Dear Waupun Area School District Community,
On April 16, 2020, the Department of Health Services Secretary-designee Andrea Palm extended the current

span.a: Safer at Home Order under Order #28

p.span: . This order extends the previous order that all K-12 schools in the state remain closed for the remainder of the 19-20 school year.

We understand that this extension raises questions for our community regarding graduation, summer school, and other items. We will work diligently to address these items and share our plans with you in a timely manner.
Your Waupun Area School District will continue with our remote learning plan. Please view via this
. We are appreciative of our families in implementing our plan and the dedication of this wonderful staff in providing excellent learning opportunities for our students.

The health, safety, and education of our students will always be the priority of your Waupun Area School District. We are better together, and we are here for you. Please contact us if you have any questions or concerns during our time apart. We miss our students and families, and we will continue to work tirelessly to provide the best remote learning possible.
We are your Waupun Area School District and we are here for you.
